We noticed you have changed the password for your account. If you didn't intend to change it, or you think someone else changed it by mistake, then we need you to contact customer service (https://www.roblox.com/support) to change the password back. That way we will know for sure that your account is secure and safe.

Please do not reply to this message. If you have any questions, please see the Roblox help page (https://www.roblox.com/help).

english: Hello,{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Your child created the account {boldTagStart}{username}{boldTagEnd} on Roblox, an online entertainment platform that enables kids to imagine, create, and play together in immersive, user-generated 3D worlds. Our platform also provides a free development tool called “Roblox Studio” that allows users to create anything they imagine, from simple drag-and-drop building experiences to complex multiplayer games. Millions of kids have used Roblox to imagine what it’s like to create the ultimate theme park, compete as a professional race car driver, star in a fashion show, or simply build a dream home and hang out with friends.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}This email is to inform you that your child has provided us with a username, date of birth, and a parent’s email address. The parent’s email address is only used for account management, password resets if the child forgets their password, and to notify parents of changes to the child’s account access. We are constantly evolving our safety features and working with digital safety experts to ensure that all players have a safe, comfortable place to play, chat, and collaborate on creative projects. We recommend that you visit our Parent’s Guide to help yourself get acquainted with our platform and find helpful tips for creating a positive experience for your kids on Roblox: {aTagStartWithHref}{parentalPageLink}{hrefEnd}{parentalPageLink}{aTagEnd}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Roblox also offers {boldTagStart}parental controls{boldTagEnd}. Parents can enable a parent PIN and change their child’s communication and chat settings. You can find these controls by visiting the security and privacy tabs in the account settings while logged into your child’s account.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}To add a parent PIN, please visit: {aTagStartWithHref}{accountSecurityLink}{hrefEnd}{accountSecurityLink}{aTagEnd}.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}To change chat settings, please visit: {aTagStartWithHref}{accountPrivacyLink}{hrefEnd}{accountPrivacyLink}{aTagEnd}.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{boldTagStart}Privacy{boldTagEnd}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}You may remove your child's account by contacting customer service at {aTagStartWithHref}{supportPageLink}{hrefEnd}{supportPageLink}{aTagEnd}. Your email will not be used for any other purpose, disclosed to third parties, or combined with any other personal information collected from your child. Please review our privacy policy for more information at {aTagStartWithHref}{privacyPageLink}{hrefEnd}{privacyPageLink}{aTagEnd}.{lineBreak}{lineBreak}{lineBreak}Thank you,{lineBreak}{lineBreak}The Roblox Team {lineBreak}{lineBreak} Do not reply to this email directly. {lineBreak}{lineBreak} {aTagStartWithHref}{robloxWebsiteLink}{hrefEnd}{robloxWebsiteLink}{aTagEnd} {lineBreak}{lineBreak} {aTagStartWithHref}{supportPageLink}{hrefEnd}{supportPageLink}{aTagEnd}

english:
Dear {username},

We noticed you have changed your email address from {oldEmailAddress} to {newEmailAddress}. If you didn't intend to change it, or you think someone else changed it by mistake, then we need you to contact customer service (https://www.roblox.com/support) to change the email back. That way we will know for sure that your account is secure and safe.

If you are happy with your new email address on Roblox you don't have to do anything! It's already set up.
Please do not reply to this message. If you have any questions please email {robloxInfoEmailAddress}.

description: Text on a button in the email verification email. Clicking this button lets the user confirm that they want this email address to be associated with their Roblox account for security purposes.

description: Informative links at the bottom of the 'email verification' email.
Subject line for the 'email verification' email for users under 13. This is sent to the parent of the user, who is responsible for taking action on authorizing the email.

First part of the body text for the 'email verification' email for users under 13. This is directed at the parent of the user. Below this text is an "I Agree, Verify Email" button that the parent can click to proceed.
english: {paragraphStart}Hello,{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}Your child created the account {emphasisStart}{username}{emphasisEnd} on Roblox, an online entertainment platform that enables kids to imagine, create, and play together in immersive, user-generated 3D worlds.{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}Your child has provided us with a username, date of birth, and a parent's email address. Please confirm this email address is correct by {emphasisStart}clicking the button below to complete the validation process{emphasisEnd}. Regardless of whether you validate the parental email address or not, the child will still be able to retain their account and chat with others.{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}By clicking the "I Agree, Validate Email" button you also agree that (a) You and your child agree to the Roblox {aTagStartWithHref}{termsOfServiceLink}{hrefEnd}Terms{aTagEnd}, including arbitration, and (b) You will supervise and be solely responsible for your child’s use of Roblox.{paragraphEnd}
translation: {paragraphStart}Hello,{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}Your child created the account {emphasisStart}{username}{emphasisEnd} on Roblox, an online entertainment platform that enables kids to imagine, create, and play together in immersive, user-generated 3D worlds.{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}Your child has provided us with a username, date of birth, and a parent's email address. Please confirm this email address is correct by {emphasisStart}clicking the button below to complete the validation process{emphasisEnd}. Regardless of whether you validate the parental email address or not, the child will still be able to retain their account and chat with others.{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}By clicking the "I Agree, Validate Email" button you also agree that (a) You and your child agree to the Roblox {aTagStartWithHref}{termsOfServiceLink}{hrefEnd}Terms{aTagEnd}, including arbitration, and (b) You will supervise and be solely responsible for your child’s use of Roblox.{paragraphEnd}

description: Text of the button in the 'email verification' email for users under 13. The text of this button is referred to by name in the first part of the email body ('by clicking "I Agree, Validate Email"...'), so the name should be consistent.

Second part of the body text in the 'email verification' email for users under 13. This is shown after a button that the parent can click to proceed with email verification. 'Parent's Guide to Roblox' and 'Privacy' are paragraph headers.
english: {paragraphStart}You can set your child's safety and parental control settings for their Roblox account at {aTagStartWithHref}{accountSettingsLink}{hrefEnd}{accountSettingsLink}{aTagEnd}.{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}{emphasisStart}Parent's Guide to Roblox{emphasisEnd}{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}We recommend that you visit our Parent’s Guide to help yourself get acquainted with our platform and find helpful tips for creating a positive experience for your kids on Roblox: {aTagStartWithHref}{parentalPageLink}{hrefEnd}{parentalPageLink}{aTagEnd}{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}{emphasisStart}Privacy{emphasisEnd}{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}You may remove your child's account anytime by contacting customer service at {aTagStartWithHref}{supportPageLink}{hrefEnd}{supportPageLink}{aTagEnd}. Your email will not be used for any other purpose, disclosed to third parties, or combined with any other personal information collected from your child. Please review our privacy policy for more information at {aTagStartWithHref}{privacyPageLink}{hrefEnd}{privacyPageLink}{aTagEnd}.{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}Thank You,{lineBreak}{emphasisStart}The Roblox Team{emphasisEnd}{paragraphEnd}
translation: {paragraphStart}You can set your child's safety and parental control settings for their Roblox account at {aTagStartWithHref}{accountSettingsLink}{hrefEnd}{accountSettingsLink}{aTagEnd}.{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}{emphasisStart}Parent's Guide to Roblox{emphasisEnd}{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}We recommend that you visit our Parent’s Guide to help yourself get acquainted with our platform and find helpful tips for creating a positive experience for your kids on Roblox: {aTagStartWithHref}{parentalPageLink}{hrefEnd}{parentalPageLink}{aTagEnd}{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}{emphasisStart}Privacy{emphasisEnd}{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}You may remove your child's account anytime by contacting customer service at {aTagStartWithHref}{supportPageLink}{hrefEnd}{supportPageLink}{aTagEnd}. Your email will not be used for any other purpose, disclosed to third parties, or combined with any other personal information collected from your child. Please review our privacy policy for more information at {aTagStartWithHref}{privacyPageLink}{hrefEnd}{privacyPageLink}{aTagEnd}.{paragraphEnd}{paragraphStart}Thank You,{lineBreak}{emphasisStart}The Roblox Team{emphasisEnd}{paragraphEnd}

description: Parental spend control launch email, Korean user over 70000 KRW limit
english: {paragraphStart}This email is to inform you that the monthly spend restrictions for account {emphasisStart}{username}{emphasisEnd} of {emphasisStart}{amountUsd} USD{emphasisEnd} per month has been changed in accordance with local regulator requirements. These regulations require that accounts held by users under the age of 18 do not spend more than 70,000 KRW per month. As a result, your monthly spend restriction has been updated to {emphasisStart}70,000 KRW{emphasisEnd}.{paragraphEnd}{lineBreak}{paragraphStart}You can make changes to your monthly spend restriction settings in {parentalControlsLinkStart}Parental Controls{linkEnd} at any time, but you will not be able to remove this restriction or set a limit above 70,000 KRW. description: Parental spend control launch email, for Korean user with limit under 70000 KRW
english: {paragraphStart}This email is to inform you that we now support setting monthly spend restrictions in your local currency, KRW. As a result, the spend restrictions for account {emphasisStart}{username}{emphasisEnd} of {emphasisStart}{amountUsd} USD{emphasisEnd} per month has been updated to {emphasisStart}{amountLocalCurrency} KRW{emphasisEnd} per month.{paragraphEnd}{lineBreak}{paragraphStart}In addition, local regulators require that accounts held by users under the age of 18 do not spend more than 70,000 KRW per month. You can make changes to your monthly spend restriction settings in {parentalControlsLinkStart}Parental Controls{linkEnd} at any time, but you will not be able to remove this restriction or set a limit above 70,000 KRW.{paragraphEnd}{lineBreak}{paragraphStart}For more information on Parental Controls, please visit the {helpCenterLinkStart}Help Center{linkEnd}.{paragraphEnd}{lineBreak}Thank you,{lineBreak}{emphasisStart}The Roblox Team{emphasisEnd}

You can make changes to your monthly spend restriction settings in {parentalControlsLinkStart}Parental Controls{linkEnd} at any time, but you will not be able to remove this restriction or set a limit above 70,000 KRW.{paragraphEnd}{lineBreak}{paragraphStart}For more information on Parental Controls, please visit the {helpCenterLinkStart}Help Center{linkEnd}.{paragraphEnd}{lineBreak}Thank you,{lineBreak}{emphasisStart}The Roblox Team{emphasisEnd}

description: Developer exchange welcome page heading
english: Welcome to the Roblox Developer Exchange!
translation: Welcome to the Roblox Developer Exchange!

english: The Developer Exchange Program (also known as DevEx) allows you to earn money by creating awesome experiences on Roblox.
translation: The Developer Exchange Program (also known as DevEx) allows you to earn money by creating awesome experiences on Roblox.

english: Once you earn {minCashoutValue} Robux or more, you are eligible to convert your virtual earnings to real-world cash.
translation: Once you earn {minCashoutValue} Robux or more, you are eligible to convert your virtual earnings to real-world cash.

english: To use DevEx, you must agree to DevEx Terms of Service and meet the simple requirements set out in those Terms, some of which are as follows:
translation: To use DevEx, you must agree to DevEx Terms of Service and meet the simple requirements set out in those Terms, some of which are as follows:

english: Minimum of {minCashoutValue} earned Robux in your account;
translation: Minimum of {minCashoutValue} earned Robux in your account;

english: 13 years of age or older; and
translation: 13 years of age or older; and

english: Community member in good standing, having complied with {termLinkStart}Roblox's Terms of Use{termLinkEnd}.
translation: Community member in good standing, having complied with {termLinkStart}Roblox's Terms of Use{termLinkEnd}.

english: You may initiate a request to exchange Robux for cash through the Developer Exchange once each calendar month.Requests are usually processed within 2 - 4 weeks. DevEx conversions are calculated in US Dollars.
translation: You may initiate a request to exchange Robux for cash through the Developer Exchange once each calendar month.Requests are usually processed within 2 - 4 weeks. DevEx conversions are calculated in US Dollars.

english: When you meet all the requirements, you will see a "Cash Out" button on this page. Click it and follow the instructions to get your payment started.
translation: When you meet all the requirements, you will see a "Cash Out" button on this page. Click it and follow the instructions to get your payment started.

english: We recommend that you familiarize yourself with the tax treatment of DevEx payments and the fees associated with different payment methods on DevEx transactions before you cash out.
translation: We recommend that you familiarize yourself with the tax treatment of DevEx payments and the fees associated with different payment methods on DevEx transactions before you cash out.

english: If your request is approved, and if this is your first time cashing out, you will receive an email inviting you to create an account on our DevEx portal. You will be prompted to enter your information at account creation.
translation: If your request is approved, and if this is your first time cashing out, you will receive an email inviting you to create an account on our DevEx portal. You will be prompted to enter your information at account creation.

english: Please make sure your information is entered accurately into the DevEx portal, and is kept up to date at all times.
translation: Please make sure your information is entered accurately into the DevEx portal, and is kept up to date at all times.

english: The information you provide is used to ensure all payments comply with laws and regulations.  Inaccuracies in information provided could impact your payment.
translation: The information you provide is used to ensure all payments comply with laws and regulations.  Inaccuracies in information provided could impact your payment.

english: Premium Payouts rewards you for making awesome experiences on Roblox that Premium subscribers love. english: Premium Payouts rewards you for making awesome games on Roblox that Premium subscribers love. If a Premium subscriber is playing your games, you’re earning a Premium payout, even if the user isn’t spending Robux in your games. These payouts are on top of what you earn from selling items in game. You can spend your payout on Roblox or you can convert it to cash if you meet the {devexLinkStart}DevEx requirements{devexLinkEnd}.
translation: Premium Payouts rewards you for making awesome games on Roblox that Premium subscribers love. If a Premium subscriber is playing your games, you’re earning a Premium payout, even if the user isn’t spending Robux in your games. These payouts are on top of what you earn from selling items in game. You can spend your payout on Roblox or you can convert it to cash if you meet the {devexLinkStart}DevEx requirements{devexLinkEnd}.

english: To see how much you’ve earned from Premium Payouts, check your {sumLinkStart}Robux history{sumLinkEnd}.
translation: To see how much you’ve earned from Premium Payouts, check your {sumLinkStart}Robux history{sumLinkEnd}.

english: To increase your Premium Payouts, you can encourage your visitors to buy Premium by building exclusive levels, items, and benefits for Premium subscribers and using the {modalLinkStart}Premium Upsell modal{modalLinkEnd} to allow them to purchase Premium in your experience.
translation: To increase your Premium Payouts, you can encourage your visitors to buy Premium by building exclusive levels, items, and benefits for Premium subscribers and using the {modalLinkStart}Premium Upsell modal{modalLinkEnd} to allow them to purchase Premium in your experience.

english: To benefit from Premium Payouts, your experience must be a free experience.
translation: To benefit from Premium Payouts, your experience must be a free experience.

english: See how many universe visits are from Premium subscribers.

english: Premium visit percentage shows you what proportion of your total visits are from Premium subscribers.

english: Increasing Premium visits helps increase your engagement score, which increases your Premium Payout.

english: Increase {startLink}Roblox Premium{endLink} users' playtime in your experience to earn payouts. {learnLinkStart}Learn more{learnLinkEnd}.

english: See how often the Premium prompt is shown in your experience and how often a visitor buys Premium from it.

english: Conversions are how many times a visitor buys Premium from your Premium upsell.
translation: Conversions are how many times a visitor buys Premium from your Premium upsell.

english: Increasing your conversion helps increase your engagement score, which increases your Premium Payout.
translation: Increasing your conversion helps increase your engagement score, which increases your Premium Payout.

english: Conversion rate is calculated as the proportion of conversions to impressions (# of conversions / # of impressions).
translation: Conversion rate is calculated as the proportion of conversions to impressions (# of conversions / # of impressions).

english: Impressions are how many times your Premium upsell is shown.
translation: Impressions are how many times your Premium upsell is shown.

english: Premium Payouts are calculated per experience based on your Premium playtime score. The Premium playtime score shows how popular your experience is among Premium subscribers as compared to other experiences. So if Premium subscribers are playing your experience more than any other experience, your Premium Payout will be higher! You can see what your Premium playtime score and Premium Payouts are in the {devStatsLinkStart}Premium Payouts chart{devStatsLinkEnd} in Developer Statistics.
translation: Premium Payouts are calculated per experience based on your Premium playtime score. The Premium playtime score shows how popular your experience is among Premium subscribers as compared to other experiences. So if Premium subscribers are playing your experience more than any other experience, your Premium Payout will be higher! You can see what your Premium playtime score and Premium Payouts are in the {devStatsLinkStart}Premium Payouts chart{devStatsLinkEnd} in Developer Statistics.

This is because the date filter at the top adjusts to your local time zone but the data points shown below are all in UTC.

english: Total amount of Robux earned by the experience in a day.
translation: Total amount of Robux earned by the experience in a day.

english: The daily revenue breakdown by source, e.g. game shop items, game passes, private servers, paid access, etc.
translation: The daily revenue breakdown by source, e.g. game shop items, game passes, private servers, paid access, etc.

english: Avg. revenue per user among all DAUs, measured by Robux, which equals Daily revenue / DAU.
translation: Avg. revenue per user among all DAUs, measured by Robux, which equals Daily revenue / DAU.

english: Avg. revenue per paying user, which equals Daily revenue / Paying users.
translation: Avg. revenue per paying user, which equals Daily revenue / Paying users.

english: % of DAUs are paying users, which equals # of paying users / DAU.
translation: % of DAUs are paying users, which equals # of paying users / DAU.

english: Breakdown filter does not apply to this chart
translation: Breakdown filter does not apply to this chart

english: DAU over time can help indicate whether players are consistently engaging with and returning to your game (related to retention). DAU can shift rapidly as a result of new features or content that you release and is a good way to measure the impact of updates on your players.
translation: DAU over time can help indicate whether players are consistently engaging with and returning to your game (related to retention). DAU can shift rapidly as a result of new features or content that you release and is a good way to measure the impact of updates on your players.

english: MAU can be maintained or grown by providing regular updates that motivate your players to continue staying in the game and addressing any issues that cause players to leave (such as bugs that cause crashes or buggy states).
translation: MAU can be maintained or grown by providing regular updates that motivate your players to continue staying in the game and addressing any issues that cause players to leave (such as bugs that cause crashes or buggy states).

english: Average session time measures how long a user plays each time they visit your game. You can compare it with your expectations based on your game design and genre. Breaking it down by age group, platform, etc. will give you an idea where to iterate your content. It can be used together with D1 retention as an early indicator of your long term retention.
translation: Average session time measures how long a user plays each time they visit your game. You can compare it with your expectations based on your game design and genre. Breaking it down by age group, platform, etc. will give you an idea where to iterate your content. It can be used together with D1 retention as an early indicator of your long term retention.

english: The # sessions and DAU can give you an idea if your game is engaging enough that attracts players to come back multiple times a day.
translation: The # sessions and DAU can give you an idea if your game is engaging enough that attracts players to come back multiple times a day.

english: This metric helps you measure the effectiveness of user acquisition efforts.
translation: This metric helps you measure the effectiveness of user acquisition efforts.

english: High Day 1 retention often leads to higher overall retention for your game. If your Day 1 Retention is low or drops, that typically means that your new user experience needs to be improved. You might be losing new players early in your game because of confusing tutorials, user interfaces, lack of immediate rewards, or a too-steep immediate progression curve.
translation: High Day 1 retention often leads to higher overall retention for your game. If your Day 1 Retention is low or drops, that typically means that your new user experience needs to be improved. You might be losing new players early in your game because of confusing tutorials, user interfaces, lack of immediate rewards, or a too-steep immediate progression curve.

english: Day 7 (D7) Retention is a good metric to track if you are hoping to make your game a daily habit - something they are motivated to play every day. If you have a low D7 retention, this may indicate an issue with engagement (new players aren't motivated to continue playing your game) or progression (players are either completing your content too quickly or taking too long to progress to the next meaningful reward).
translation: Day 7 (D7) Retention is a good metric to track if you are hoping to make your game a daily habit - something they are motivated to play every day. If you have a low D7 retention, this may indicate an issue with engagement (new players aren't motivated to continue playing your game) or progression (players are either completing your content too quickly or taking too long to progress to the next meaningful reward).

english: D30 retention helps you understand the effectiveness of converting new players to regular players.
translation: D30 retention helps you understand the effectiveness of converting new players to regular players.

english: D1 stickiness indicates the overall engagement and retention for both new and returning players who play the game every day. It can be used to understand the impact of your updates.
translation: D1 stickiness indicates the overall engagement and retention for both new and returning players who play the game every day. It can be used to understand the impact of your updates.

english: D7 stickiness can serve as an early indicator of whether your updates lead to long term retention for your overall player base.
translation: D7 stickiness can serve as an early indicator of whether your updates lead to long term retention for your overall player base.

english: D30 stickiness, along with D30 retention, gives a full picture of long term retention for your game.
translation: D30 stickiness, along with D30 retention, gives a full picture of long term retention for your game.

english: Revenue, or total Robux earned, is the easiest metric to track for monetization. Knowing how many of your players are willing to pay money in your game and how much your players are willing to spend, among other key metrics, will allow you to understand the health of the monetization in your game and to adjust your monetization strategy more effectively.
translation: Revenue, or total Robux earned, is the easiest metric to track for monetization. Knowing how many of your players are willing to pay money in your game and how much your players are willing to spend, among other key metrics, will allow you to understand the health of the monetization in your game and to adjust your monetization strategy more effectively.

english: ARPDAU is one of the key metrics to track for monetization. You can understand the value of each player in your game and use it to estimate the change in revenue you’ll see as your DAU and MAU change over time.
translation: ARPDAU is one of the key metrics to track for monetization. You can understand the value of each player in your game and use it to estimate the change in revenue you’ll see as your DAU and MAU change over time.

english: ARPPU focuses on the players who are willing to pay for your game and is most useful when considered alongside your conversion rate. Players who buy something in your game once are often more likely to buy again. A high ARPPU typically means that your paying players are finding high, repeat value in your game and is also indicative of high player engagement.
translation: ARPPU focuses on the players who are willing to pay for your game and is most useful when considered alongside your conversion rate. Players who buy something in your game once are often more likely to buy again. A high ARPPU typically means that your paying players are finding high, repeat value in your game and is also indicative of high player engagement.

english: Understanding what’s valuable in your game to players can help you figure out what to sell, how to set prices for players with varying wallet sizes, and how to design progression and economy to encourage that first purchase, and then to create longer-term paying users.
translation: Understanding what’s valuable in your game to players can help you figure out what to sell, how to set prices for players with varying wallet sizes, and how to design progression and economy to encourage that first purchase, and then to create longer-term paying users.

english: ARPDAU and ARPPU are most useful when considered alongside your conversion rate. Conversion rate reflects how well you are able to motivate players to spend money in your game.  If you have a high conversion rate, for example, and a low ARPPU, that indicates that you are good at getting players to buy at least one item in your game, but that there is little beyond that initial purchase that inspires further spending. Understanding what is inspiring that first-time purchase and examining its value could help you determine what content you need to create to inspire more purchases.
translation: ARPDAU and ARPPU are most useful when considered alongside your conversion rate. Conversion rate reflects how well you are able to motivate players to spend money in your game.  If you have a high conversion rate, for example, and a low ARPPU, that indicates that you are good at getting players to buy at least one item in your game, but that there is little beyond that initial purchase that inspires further spending. Understanding what is inspiring that first-time purchase and examining its value could help you determine what content you need to create to inspire more purchases.

english: This metric helps you understand your important revenue driver so that strategically choose the area to optimize for.
translation: This metric helps you understand your important revenue driver so that strategically choose the area to optimize for.

english: Monetization refers to your ability to earn money from players. The KPIs help you generate actionable insights to optimize your monetization.
translation: Monetization refers to your ability to earn money from players. The KPIs help you generate actionable insights to optimize your monetization.

english: The data is net revenue (i.e. after the fees from Roblox and the original creators), does not include refund info, and is delayed by 2 days instead of 1 day for retention and engagement metrics.
translation: The data is net revenue (i.e. after the fees from Roblox and the original creators), does not include refund info, and is delayed by 2 days instead of 1 day for retention and engagement metrics.

english: Roblox is committed to making its websites usable by all people, including those with disabilities by meeting or exceeding the requirements of the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1 Level A/AA (WCAG 2.1 A/AA).  We strive to make our sites an equal experience for everyone.{lineBreak}We continue to monitor our sites and make sure that all content provided is accessible to all visitors. english:
When posting public content (including Job Posts and Creator Pages), you are not permitted to request users directly contact you outside of the platform. This includes posting email addresses, usernames for other platforms, or telephone numbers.

Interactions on Talent Hub must start with a Talent Hub Job Application (“Application”) but may then move to another communication platform after the Job Creator indicates they are “Interested” in connecting after reviewing the Job Seeker’s application. You may only provide instructions to connect with a user on another platform within the private Application chat. Please note, however, that Roblox is not able to mediate disputes arising from communications or interactions that take place off of Roblox.
translation:
When posting public content (including Job Posts and Creator Pages), you are not permitted to request users directly contact you outside of the platform. This includes posting email addresses, usernames for other platforms, or telephone numbers.

Interactions on Talent Hub must start with a Talent Hub Job Application (“Application”) but may then move to another communication platform after the Job Creator indicates they are “Interested” in connecting after reviewing the Job Seeker’s application. You may only provide instructions to connect with a user on another platform within the private Application chat. Please note, however, that Roblox is not able to mediate disputes arising from communications or interactions that take place off of Roblox.
